Active Directory Audit & Reporting
Overview

This module provides a PowerShell-based audit of an Active Directory environment, focusing on security posture, account hygiene, and operational visibility.

It identifies common risks such as inactive accounts, excessive privileges, and misconfigured policies, and outputs structured reports for review.

Key Features:
-Detects inactive user accounts (based on last logon)
-Identifies accounts with passwords set to never expire
-Reports disabled user accounts
-Enumerates privileged group membership
-Finds stale computer accounts
-Generates CSV reports + JSON summary

.
├── Invoke-ADAudit.ps1      # Main audit script
├── reports/                # Generated audit outputs
└── README.md               # This file

How It Works:
The script queries Active Directory and evaluates objects against common administrative and security checks:

Check			| 	Description
Inactive Users			Accounts with no logon activity beyond a defined threshold
Password Never Expires		Accounts bypassing standard password policy
Disabled Users			Accounts no longer in use but still present
Privileged Users		Members of high-impact groups (e.g., Domain Admins)
Stale Computers			Machines that have not authenticated recently


Usage
Run with default settings (30-day inactivity threshold)
.\Invoke-ADAudit.ps1
Customize inactivity threshold
.\Invoke-ADAudit.ps1 -InactiveDays 60

Reports are generated in the ./reports directory:

inactive-users-<timestamp>.csv
password-never-expires-<timestamp>.csv
disabled-users-<timestamp>.csv
privileged-users-<timestamp>.csv
stale-computers-<timestamp>.csv
summary-<timestamp>.json

The summary file provides a quick overview of key metrics:

Total users
Number of inactive accounts
Privileged users
Other flagged conditions
Example Use Case

This script simulates a routine administrative audit to:

Identify unnecessary access
-Highlight policy violations
-Support cleanup and remediation efforts
-Design Considerations
-Read-only operations (safe to run in any environment)
-Modular checks (easy to extend with additional audits)
-Structured outputs for reporting and analysis
-Configurable thresholds for flexibility

Key Learnings
-Querying and filtering AD objects with PowerShell
-Identifying common security risks in directory services
-Producing structured, audit-friendly reports
-Translating administrative tasks into automation

Future Improvements
-Integration with SIEM or logging systems

Disclaimer

This project is intended for lab and demonstration purposes. It does not represent a complete enterprise security audit solution.